Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <JiveBuddha> Is 1 hush to 10,000 memos a fixed rate or a calculation of some current variable network expense?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <JiveBuddha> A fixed rate for something like that is really bad

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @JiveBuddha 0.0001 is the default transaction fee, so 10,000 "normal" transaction fees = 1 HUSH

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> if/when the Hush network gets busier, fees will inevitably increase, but that likely won't happen for a while

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Zcash itself has mostly empty blocks, and it has smaller blocks than Hush

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> so 10K memos per Hush is just a convenient rough estimate. it's possible to pay 0 fee still on the Hush network, but I wouldn't bet your private future communications on that. You can also pay a tiny tiny fee and maybe make 1M memos from 1 HUSH, but that is up for miners to decide

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @JiveBuddha i agree, fixed rates are bad
